how to change dns server

dns name is stored in "/etc/resolv.conf" here in linux

to change simply change the nameserver in the file.

somedns server:

    1.1.1.1 +> cloudfare (recomended)
    8.8.8.8 +> google (not recomended)
    
Public DNS Servers

    cloudfare => 
            1.1.1.1         2606:4700:4700::1111
            1.0.0.1         2606:4700:4700::1001
    
    OpenDNS =>
            208.67.222.222
            208.67.220.220
    
    Norton DNS =>
            198.153.192.1
            198.153.194.1
        
    Google Public DNS => (not recomended)
            8.8.8.8
            8.8.4.4         

    
     
  
   
